101638,variable,Piper-THRYVE-Out-Wheels,,Piper THRYVE Wheels,1,0,visible,"Piper THRYVE, the ultimate urban speed wheel!","Two-component wheels, made of some of the toughest and most resilient TPU cores and polyurethane available to mankind. Manufactured by Aend Industries located in Hutto, TX USA, owner of Piper Wheels and the most prolific urethane manufacturing company in the world. Still to this day, Neal Piper, our in-house chemist and engineer holds all two-component speed world records using his special recipes.

column2: • TPU core – Glass fused with urethane for unparalleled strength and performance.
• Speed profile – more agility and speed combined.

column1: 102622,variable,FR-FR380BlueFreerideSkate,,FR FR3 80 Blue Freeride Skate,1,0,visible,"The FR FR3 80 Inline Skate is a great for those that want a low cost boot with the capability to improve their skills in all skating styles.
\nPRE ORDER","FR FR3 80 Blue Freeride Skates

\nThe New FR3 80 is the perfect skate to combine FReeride and FReestyle skating in only one model. Thanks to their X3R rockerable frames, you just need to turn the axles to get more maneuverability to practice FReestyle or more stability for enjoy FReeride.
\nThanks to the integrated plates, you will gain in stability and precision.
\nThe FR3 is a great skate to improve your skills in all skating styles.
\nCompared to its older version, this model is equipped with:

column2: • X3R frames, new dimensions for a lower balance and updated design. (not compatible with the old FR3 shell)
• 4mm mounting screws (standard Allen key for tightening)

column1: \nPlease note: The Standard FR BRAKE IS NOT COMPATIBLE with the X3R frame, but a specific brake model will be available first semester 2025.

The new FR FR3 80 White is the newer skates in the FR family.

The FR FR3 80 Inline Skates is build for skaters that want a low cost boot with the capability to grow and develop a great skating skill.

They FR FR3 80 White feature

  • A new upgraded FR Liner
  • A new X2R frames\, providing better control and response for all types of inline skating. 2 buckles Strap
  • 7-hole mounting; the micro-ratchet to allow different positioning and sizing of frames
  • Plastic Shell/ Plastich Cuff 4 positions
  • Double strap + FK Aluminum Top Buckle
  • X2 R Rockerable Aluminum frame
  • the frame is compatible with 310 and 325 set up
  • Wheels Street King 80mm/85A
  • Twincam Abec 7 bearings

Best used for:

Freeride\, Street\, freestyle and City skating.

105765,variable,Edea-Flamenco-Rollline-Giotto-Combo,,Edea Flamenco Giotto Skate No toe Stop Combo,1,0,visible,,"The Edea Flamenco Giotto combos are designed to be customized by you and are priced to give you a good deal without sacrificing choice.

\nFor most skaters a standard mount is preferred, placing the front axle under the ball of the foot. A short mount, placing the front axle behind the ball of the foot, is recommended for loops. Freestyle skates are generally long-mounted with the front axle in front of the ball of the foot.

\nIf you select mounting for the Edea Flamenco Giotto, you are agreeing that: I am certain that I have selected the correct size(s). I acknowledge that all sales of mounted combos/packages are final and that they are not eligible for refund OR exchange.

\n
",,,taxable,,1,,,0,0,10.0,16,14.0,6.0,0,,,,"Roller Skates > Edea Roller Skate, Roller Skates > Edea Roller Skate > Edea Skate Packages, Roller Skates",,,"http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/FLAMENCO-GIOTTO-COMBO-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/FLAMENCO-GIOTTO-COMBO-white-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/FLAMENCO-GIOTTO-COMBO-black-scaled.jpg",,,,,,,,,0,,,,Boot Color,"Black, White",1.0,1.0,Boot size,"225, 230, 235, 240, 245, 250, 255, 260, 265, 270, 275, 280, 285, 290, 295, 300, 305, 310",1.0,1.0,,,,,,,,,,"The Edea Flamenco is the ultimate dance skating boot for upper levels in roller skating.
The Edea Flamenco is an ultralight and very soft roller construction with a beautiful leather finish outside and a perforated microfiber lining.
The Edea Flamenco is made with revolutionary NEW ultra-lightweight materials, which means that the Flamenco is 25% to 45% lighter than comparable skating boots.
The Edea Flamenco has been specially designed for roller dancing and is extremely comfortable.
Size: 225 to 310 in 5 mm increments, available in full and half sizes
Color: Ivory White and Ivory Black
Training Level: Entry level through senior level Roller Dancers
Comfort level: This is an extremely comfortable boot.
Technical Specification
Size: 225 to 310 in 5 mm increments, available in full and half sizes
Color: Ivory White and Ivory Black
Training Level: Entry level through senior level Roller Dancers
Comfort level: This is an extremely comfortable boot.
Skaters often choose boots by matching their standard shoe size with what they believe is the equivalent size in skates.
Unfortunately these two sizing systems do not always correspond exactly, because each manufacturer has its own
measuring type, and also because standard shoes, which require the foot to bend, are usually longer than skates.
For these reasons we recommend that you always choose the size of your boots based on a real measurement.
the length of the foot, matching this to the inner length of the boot.
For purely illustrative purposes only, below we have provided a table comparing sizes in MILLIMETERS to the
different scales of sizes relative to standard shoes.
The Roll-Line Giotto Professional Figure Skate is the most accurate and articulate skate available today.
The Giotto is the professional skate that is winning more world figure titles than any other skate.
The Giotto Professional Figure Skate provides the best possible performance due to its innovative design and ultra-lightweight structure.

The Roll-Line Giotto Professional Figure Skate (just like the Energy Titanium and Energy Steel) is forged from a solid bar of Ergal Aluminum Alloy and completely CNC machined. Ergal is one of the strongest and lightest aluminum alloys available and has a lower expansion coefficient and offers the best coiled-spring response.

The Roll-Line Click Action adjustment system provides optimum, accurate, articulate, and consistent action adjustments using the 04 series, 13 mm base kingpins with adjustment click-nuts and locking screws. The Giotto features the strongest steel axles available and adjustable pivot pins. The Giotto is an Energy Steel without a toe stop mount.

The design and materials of Roll-Line Skates provide athletes the proper support of the skating shoe and give the most sensitive control and the greatest and absolutely fastest response available from any skate, providing a sense of excellent stability and action.
Roll-Line Natural Rubber and Urethane Suspensions provide rapid and fluid energy transmission from the foot through the skate to the skating surface.","Roll Line Giotto Plate:
Since the Giotto frame is a product constructed exclusively for professional use, it guarantees the best performance only when correctly adjusted.
An optimal position is achieved by carefully choosing the most appropriate suspensions in relation to the type of skating and the weight of the athlete.
Turn the action adjustment nut with the 17 mm wrench in the clockwise direction to make the action more rigid, or in the counterclockwise direction to make it softer.
It is essential to check that the pivot is well inserted into the pivot bush while exerting slight pressure.
The adjustment The nut locking screw is only a safe screw; remove it only when you change the suspensions.
Loosen the pivot locking screw with a 13 mm wrench.
Screw the pivot on or off with a 6 mm wrench until this is well inserted into the pivot bush while exerting slight pressure. Retighten the pivot locking screw.
We recommend that you check the status of the various components every time this product is used. In particular, carefully check the following:
- that the plate is well fastened to the boot;
- that the bolts are well fastened to the plate of the skate;
- the wear and tear status of the suspensions;
- that the pivot is well inserted into the pivot bush with slight pressure;
- the wear and tear status of the wheels and the self-locking nuts for fastening the wheels;
- the optimal gliding of the bearings;
- the wear and tear status, correct position, proper closure, and the cleanliness of the toe stop feature.","

The Roll-Line Giotto Professional Figure Skate is the most Accurate and Articulate Skate available today.
The Giotto is the Professional Skate that is winning more World Figure Titles than any other Skate.
The Giotto Professional Figure Skate provides the best possible performance due to its innovative design and ultra-lightweight structure.

The Roll-Line Giotto Professional Figure Skate (just like the Energy Titanium and Energy Steel) is forged from a solid bar of Ergal Aluminum Alloy and completely CNC machined. Ergal is one of the Strongest and Lightest Aluminum Alloys available and has a lower expansion coefficient and offers the best coiled-spring response.

The Roll-Line Click Action adjustment system provides optimum, accurate, articulate, and consistent Action adjustments using the 04 series, 13mm base King Pins with Adjustment Click-Nuts and Locking Screws. The Giotto features the strongest Steel Axles available and adjustable Pivot Pins. The Giotto is an Energy Steel without a Toe Stop mount.

The design and materials of Roll-Line Skates provide athletes the proper support of the skating shoe and give the most sensitive control, the greatest and absolute fastest response available from any skate, providing a sense of excellent stability and action.
Roll-Line Natural Rubber and Urethane Suspensions provide rapid and fluid energy transmission from the foot through the skate to the skating surface.","Roll Line Giotto Plate:
Since the Giotto frame is a product constructed exclusively for professional use, it guarantees the best performance only when correctly adjusted.
An optimal position is achieved by carefully choosing the most Appropriate suspensions in relation to the type of skating and the weight of the athlete.
Turn the action adjustment nut with the 17 mm wrench in the clockwise direction to make the action more rigid, or in the counter clockwise direction to make it softer.
It is essential to check that the pivot is well inserted into the pivot bush while exerting slight pressure.
The adjustment Nut locking screw is only a safe screw, remove it only when you change the suspensions.
Loosen the pivot locking screw with a 13 mm wrench.
Screw the pivot on or off with a 6 mm wrench until this is well inserted into the pivot bush while exerting slight pressure. Retighten the pivot locking screw.
We recommend that you check the status of the various components every time this product is used. In particular, carefully check the following:
- that the plate is well fastened to the boot;
- that the bolts are well fastened to the plate of the skate;
- the wear and tear status of the suspensions;
- that the pivot is well inserted into the pivot bush with slight pressure;
- the wear and tear status of the wheels and the self-locking nuts for fastening the wheels;
- the optimal gliding of the bearings;
- the wear and tear status, correct position, proper closure and the cleanliness of the toe stop feature.","

Features
Jackson VIP Rink Skate:
The Jackson skate company has been a global leader in the figure skating industry for the past 20 years.

A few years ago the Jackson decided to get involved in the Roller Derby world by introducing the Elite, Competitor, and Vantage leather boots.

The Jackson joint venture with Atom alias Luigino skate to put together some exciting derby skate and recreational quad skates.

The Jackson VIP outdoor skate is perfect for fitness skaters and beginners.
The New Vantage boot has a high-quality Microfiber with an exceptional fit.
The VIP Rink Roller skate features:

Piper WHIPLASH Indoor Wheels 

The Piper Whiplash is Indoor\, flat-track racing\, America’s Formula-1 for inline speed skating.

Pushing boundaries in the flat-track speed skating world remains Piper's leading focus. From Hyper Octane to Atom IQ to our most current Duo-Tech\, Neal Piper has redesigned\, retooled\, and reinvigorated a new generation of race wheels…again!

Whiplash M-Disc is made with reinforced engineered thermoplastic content that provides rigid\, responsive handling not available in our previous flat-track indoor wheels. Duo Technology is the central engine that separates Piper wheels from others. 


Features:

  • M-Disc: Spoke design provides stiffness and rigidity for high-speed turns
  • Duo-Tech: 2-n-1 (Two wheels in one)\, our central engine
  • Duo-Tech\, casted with supercharged soft urethane
  • Divergent core: flex-return\, enhances steerability\, and easy of skating
  • SuperThane tire formula: Magnifies energy & longevity
  • Size: 110 M-Disc 74 mm/speed profile
  • Size: 100 Velocity core 64mm /speed profile matches 110
  • Size 90 Velocity core 54mm: no insert\, same formula\, speed profile

113876,variable,BackSpinAstro53MM,,BackSpin Astro 58MM Roller Skate Wheels,1,0,visible,"VNLA Backspin Astro wheels, one of the lightest wheels in the market.","BackSpin Astro Roller Skate Wheels

\nBackspin Astro is one of the lightest roller skate wheels on the market.  It features a high strength aircraft aluminum CNC hub, that is guaranteed not to crack or flex.  In addition to the high spec aluminum hub, Backspin is using their all new high-grip 96-98A urethane.

\nThe Astro is offered in two sizes,  58x38mm  and 65x43mm.  The MINI 58mm wheel is ideal for jam skaters and derby players looking for lower center of gravity and quicker transitions.   The taller 65mm wheels are perfect for speed and shuffle skaters,  where speed is desired.
\nKeeping with Vanilla’s jam skating heritage, we know looking good is important. That’s why every set of Astro wheels includes a matching set of jam plugs and a reusable wheel box.
\n(Priced as set of 8)

\n",,,taxable,,1,,,0,0,3.0,7,7.0,5.0,0,,,,"Roller Skates > Roller Skate Wheels > Backspin Vanilla Roller Skate Wheels, Roller Skates > Vanilla Skates > Backspin Wheels, Roller Skates > Roller Skate Wheels",,,"http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Backspin-Astro-pinkgreen-wheels-main-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Backspin-Astro-pink-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Backspin-Astro-Green-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Backspin-Astro-Pink-2-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Backspin-Astro-Green-2-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Backspin-astro-Pink-3-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Backspin-Astro-Green-3-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Astro-wheels-Orange-scaled.jpg, http://rollerskateusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/astro-wheels-yellow-scaled.jpg",,,,,BackSpinDeluxe,,,,0,,,,ExtraField 1,Backspin Deluxe wheels with Aluminum Hub,1.0,0.0,ExtraField 6,"Backspin Deluxe Wheels

114962,variable,UniQEraRollSkatePack-1,,UniQ Era Colors Roller Skate Package,1,0,visible,"An amazing choice, designed for serious speed, shuffle, or jam skaters as well as rink skaters who take their skating seriously.","
UniQ Era Roller Skate Package

\n
Introducing the new UniQ Era Skate Package

\n
The Uniq Era skaters were born by an infusion of traditional and UniQ technologies by using Dream-Last Barefoot technology and exclusive Flex-Fit Tech combined with traditional machine lasting.

\n

This quad-speed skate is designed for serious speed, shuffle, or jam skaters as well as rink skaters. It is an amazing choice for skaters who take their skating seriously.
\nThis skate is unique as well because you will be able to add some personality by using the removable lace covers that come in 9 different colors!
\nLace Cover Colors: Black/Gold, Black/Metallic pink, Black/White, Green/Black, Orange/Black, Pink/Black, Red/Silver, Purple/Pink, White/White.

\n
Best for Speed, shuffle, Jam, and Rink Skating.

UniQ Era Roller Skate Package

Features:

-Boots: The Icon 180 features Flex-Fit heel cups\, Flex-Fit counters\, 

Hand-Lasting for supreme fit\, external heels for the optimum heel lift\, 

and UniQ footbeds for increased performance. 

-Chassis: Rock double-action plates with adjustable toe stops. 

-Wheels: Piper Freaky Fast 62mm x 44mm SpeedThane wheels. 

-Bearings: ABEC-7.

",1.0,0.0,,,,,,,UniQ DAY Roller Skate Package,,
Feature
UniQ DAY Roller Skate Package,"ERA – Infused tradition and UniQ technologies starting with our exclusive “Dream-Last” Barefoot technology and UniQ Flex-Fit Tech combined with traditional machine lasting. UniQ’s ‘NEW ERA’ is born.

column2: • Removable Lace covers! Available in 9 different colors

• Robust Responsive Outsole: One piece outsole made of composite material giving ERA a rigid foundation with robust response and energy return. One piece outsole significantly reduces the weight of the boot.

• The composite outsole is designed and manufactured specifically for UniQ Barefoot-Last, giving it an ergonomic fit. By using composite materials, there is no need for a midsole, thus reducing the weight significantly.

• UniQ footbeds also designed and manufactured specifically for UniQ Barefoot-Last that hug and support the natural contours of the foot. By contrast, old school quad boots are typically made with a midsole that increases the weight, creates a very stiff instep resulting in pain, numbness, cramping and reduces overall performance.
• Premium microfiber uppers give the boot a soft feel and tough skin that doesn’t stretch -forms to your foot and stays supple.
• Premium super-soft microfiber lining that stays soft under most conditions, comfortably holds your foot in place.

• EGO Wheels by Piper: Size 62X44, Hardness 95A, utility wheel made of high-performance, high rebound urethane. Great for all indoor surfaces (wood, cement, tile, etc.). Use: jam, shuffle, derby, speed, fitness and recreation.
• UniQ Bearings: ABEC 7 – Precision bearings, 8mm, light oil, low maintenance.

• UniQ Plate: All new high-performance plate system incorporates our proven geometry that optimizes speed, maneuverability and stability with simplicity. Stripped down truck system, integrated toe-stop insert, less parts, lightweight, stronger, more dependable. Whether you are speed, park, jam, rhythm, dance, derby or a hard core all-skate junky, you need a plate that delivers the perfect balance of strength, stiffness, weight and agility.

column1: • UniQ Composite: Molded, toe stop insert

• UniQ nylon – DuPont, reinforced composite base plate (LGF)Overcoming Challenges of Metal-to-PlasticUniQ composite plate: Plastics elongation and toughness is an advantage over metal that enables them to absorb higher impact stresses and resist permanent deformation or denting at impact locations. Elongation and toughness also gives plastics excellent cyclical fatigue endurance over metals.LGF = Long Glass Fiber “Boosting Performance without Breaking the Bank”

Among the plastic compounds are fiber-reinforced plastics, these come in two main variants with either short fiber reinforcement made with chopped fiber or long fiber reinforcement made from continuous fiber. Fiber reinforcement can provide a tremendous amount of structural integrity and raise the tensile strength of the entry-level engineering polymer nylon 6/6 (polyamide 6/6) six times from 8,000 psi (55 MPa) up to 48,000 psi (331 MPa). This puts plastic strength in the same performance realm as metals like die-cast magnesium and aluminum. Of the two types of fiber-reinforced plastics, short fiber filled compounds are best at providing low to moderate levels of performance enhancement while long fiber-reinforced composites are better at providing moderate to high levels of performance making them well suited for most metal replacement situations.

The Bont Press features:

  • Use: Inline\, Scooter or Quad wheels. Maximum diameter 125mm
  • Material: 6061 aluminum and steel 
  • Bearing size: 8mm bearings
This bearing press can be used with any brand of inline skate wheels.

Feature
Bont 125mm Inline Skate Bearing press,"
Built to Last:

Crafted with the same meticulous attention to detail as our renowned skates, this backpack is built to endure. The heavy-duty, water-resistant exterior shields your gear from the elements, while reinforced stitching and durable zippers ensure longevity.

Never worry about your skates getting damaged in transit. Our dedicated skate compartments feature adjustable straps to securely hold inline, roller, hockey skates or ice skates of various sizes. The padded interior protects your blades and boots, keeping them pristine.

We understand that skaters carry a lot of gear. That's why we've designed this backpack with multiple compartments and pockets to accommodate everything you need. The main compartment easily fits a helmet and pads, while additional pockets keep your clothing, water bottle, tools, and personal items organized and within reach.

Whether commuting to the skatepark or embarking on a skating adventure, comfort is key. The padded back panel and shoulder straps, along with the adjustable chest strap, distribute weight evenly and reduce strain on your back and shoulders. You'll barely notice you're carrying a full load.

Bont has been a trusted name in the skating world for decades. Our commitment to quality and performance is reflected in every product we create, including this premium skate backpack. Invest in the best and experience the difference a well-designed backpack can make in your skating life.

column2: • 2 axles bolts to attach brake to the frame

column1: This Bont inline skate brake works really well for skaters who love speed skates but miss having a brake that they are used to using on their rollerblades or recreational skates. Most rollerblades and recreational skates come with a brake so skaters get familiar with using it to come to a stop. Speedskaters will normally use a snowplow walking technique to come to a stop but until you can learn how to do this, a heel brake is a good idea. The rubber on this brake is long-lasting and replaceable.

Envy Carbon Roller Skate Boot

Built with a durable synthetic outer skin that holds up to intense skating sessions, the Envy features a strong carbon composite base. This combination creates a responsive boot that gives skaters the control they need.
Made with jam skaters in mind, the Envy's low-profile design helps you confidently flow through your moves. A practical lace cover keeps things neat and tidy while you're focused on your skating.

The Envy strikes an ideal balance between support and mobility. Its thoughtful construction keeps your feet comfortable during long sessions while maintaining the responsiveness needed for technical skating.
The heat-moldable design lets you customize the fit to your exact foot shape. This personalization process means your boots will feel like they were made just for you.

Unleash Your Skating Potential with the Bont Royal Assassin Wheels

,"

\n

Bont Royal Assassin Roller Skate Wheels

\n
The Bont Royal Assassin Wheel is here to redefine your skating experience. Crafted with meticulous attention to detail and cutting-edge materials, these wheels epitomize performance and innovation.

column2: • Unlike mass-produced wheels, the Royal Assassin Wheel features a premium urethane formula developed by renowned urethane expert Scott Corey. This exotic urethane delivers unparalleled rebound, grip, and durability, elevating your skating to new heights.
• The Royal Assassin's urethane is gravity poured, ensuring a perfect distribution and eliminating inconsistencies often found in injected wheels.
• Aircraft-Grade Aluminum: The Royal Assassin Wheel boasts a 6061 aircraft-grade aluminum hub for maximum strength, rebound, and a precise bearing seat.
• Lightweight Design: Extensive machining reduces unnecessary weight, resulting in a hub that is both incredibly strong and remarkably light.

column1:
\n

Optimized Shape and Grooves for Instant Performance

column2: • Skater-Informed Design: The shape of the Royal Assassin Wheel, especially the lip, has been meticulously crafted based on feedback from top skaters, ensuring a feel that translates to instant performance.
• Unique Grooving Pattern: The grooving pattern, featuring a double-cut design, virtually eliminates break-in time, allowing you to unleash the full potential of the wheels right out of the box.

column1: \nDue to the intricate production process and the use of premium materials, the Bont Royal Assassin Wheels are available in extremely limited quantities. Don't miss out on the opportunity to experience the pinnacle of roller skate wheel technology.

Embrace the Uniqueness: Handcrafted Bont Royal Assassin Wheels

Our commitment to crafting high-performance wheels by hand means that each Bont Royal Assassin wheel is a unique creation, shaped by artistry and the nature of our premium urethane. While we strive for excellence, the handmade process and materials can result in subtle variations that add character and authenticity to your wheels.
Here are a few natural occurrences you might expect:

column2: • Air Bubbles Our high-performance urethane may contain tiny air bubbles, a natural part of the manufacturing process. These are harmless and won't affect performance. We have specific criteria to ensure these bubbles are minimal:
• Skate surface: Up to 3 bubbles, each 3mm or smaller, not grouped together.
• Wheel Face and Lip: Up to 2 bubbles, each 2mm or smaller, not grouped together.
• Back of the wheel: Up to 2 bubbles, each 4mm or smaller, not grouped together.

column1: Streaks The face of the wheel may exhibit subtle streaks, adding a unique visual touch.
Slight Hub Scratches Before pouring the urethane, the hub is prepared through sandblasting and priming. A clamp during this process can sometimes leave a tiny imperfection on the hub.
Grooves We hand-buff the grooves in each wheel, ensuring a faster break-in period. This personal touch means each wheel will be slightly different, showcasing the artistry of the final buff.

These natural variations are not defects; they are a testament to the handcrafted nature of your Bont Royal Assassin wheels. They add to the charm and individuality of each wheel, making them truly one-of-a-kind.
Sold in 8 packs

119813,variable,BONTFXX2RollerWheels,,BONT FXX Roller Skate Wheels,1,0,visible,"

FXX wheels are an improved version of the original FXX roller skate wheels, with enhanced features for optimal performance.

","

\n

BONT FXX Roller Skate Wheels

\nIntroducing the highly acclaimed Bont FXX roller skate wheels, now available in exclusive limited edition runs featuring various sizes, hardness levels, and vibrant colors. Act fast to secure your order – each release is one of a kind, and we may not offer the same wheel twice.
\nThese FXX wheels are an improved version of the original FXX roller skate wheels, with enhanced features for optimal performance.

\nThe FXX is a lightweight performance wheel that features high-quality urethane and an aluminum hub for the ultimate combination of grip and roll. Made with the best urethane in the USA, the FXX uses a technical 5-spoke hub for lightweight, premium performance. The aluminum hub allows for unparalleled stiffness and control, which translates to brilliant edging and maximum agility.

\nThe FXX comes in two hardnesses 92a and 96a, with excellent rebound and wear properties. They are super fast and phenomenally grippy while still allowing you to skid to a stop instantly. The 59x38mm size lets you change speeds quicker, making them the perfect choice for derby skating. The 62x44mm size gives you a larger surface for longer pushes for maximum power, making them the best choice for speed skating.

\nDrawing on our inline speed skating wheel that has won multiple inline world championships, we adapted one of our top inline speed wheel formulas on the FXX for roller skating. This is unheard of in a roller skate wheel. No one uses the best inline racing formulas in roller skate wheels. When we spoke to wheel makers about using a top inline formula in a roller skate wheel this is what they said: 'It will cost too much, roller skaters don't want to pay over $200 for a set of wheels no matter how good they are'. 'Roller skaters can't tell the difference between a high-end or low-end urethane'. And 'our standard high-end roller skate urethane is good enough'. We said 'screw that' and started testing wheels using more exotic urethanes previously only reserved for inline racers. The result, in our opinion, is the best mass-produced roller skate wheel ever made. We are sure you will appreciate the effort that we put in to bring this wheel to market.

Feature
Powerslide ACCEL carbon Inline Skate Frame,"
Features

The MG Frame frame collection is one of the most recognized and successful inline race frame. With a length of 13.0 inches / 330mm and designed to roll on 3x125mm wheels, the frame is the ideal for racing, and for skaters looking for unmatched inline racing performance. This superb Triskate frame is made of light and durable magnesium machined to perfection. The frame weights only 161 grams due to the magnesium used. Designed to deliver efficient power transfer with every stride, the MG Frame 3x125, 13,0"" frame will help you reaching the top of the podium in no time. Introducing the revolutionary Swings Speed Frames: meticulously crafted from the finest-grade Magnesium, each frame is fully extruded and precision-machined to absolute perfection. Every surface and edge is a testament to the artistry of CNC work, embodying Bart's vision of a frame that's both supremely stiff and feather-light. Engineered for optimum performance, these frames feature wider deck mounting for flawless power transfer and direct flat side walls for an exceptionally efficient push. The attention to detail is unparalleled, with an exquisite finish and intricate printed designs showcasing Swings' dedication to craftsmanship. Available in a range of sizes, the Swings Speed Frames are already making waves in the racing scene, proving their worth on the track even before their official release. With their low profile, lightweight construction, and unbeatable stiffness, these frames offer seamless edge-to-edge movement and unparalleled push efficiency. Designed to provide stiffness where it's needed and flexibility where it counts, the Swings Speed Frames are set to revolutionize the world of speed skating. Experience the difference for yourself and elevate your performance to new heights with Swings. Introducing Swings Speed Axles: the epitome of lightweight performance and precision engineering. Crafted from premium AL 7075 aluminum, these axles boast a CNC-cut middle section, ensuring optimal weight reduction without compromising strength. Finished to perfection with a luxurious gold anodized coating, Swings Speed Axles not only enhance the aesthetics of your skates but also elevate your performance on the track. Their lightweight design reduces rotational mass, allowing for quicker acceleration and smoother transitions. Engineered for durability and speed, these axles provide the perfect balance of strength and agility. Whether you're racing towards the finish line or mastering intricate maneuvers, Swings Speed Axles deliver unparalleled performance with every stride. Upgrade your skating experience with Swings Speed Axles – where lightness meets strength, and performance meets perfection. Introducing Swings Spacers – a masterpiece of precision engineering. Each spacer is meticulously crafted with a 360° CNC cut, creating a stunning visual reminiscent of a saw cutting through wood. Designed with a focus on weight reduction, these spacers are the epitome of lightweight performance. Weighing in at only 1.0g, they are the lightest aluminum spacers on the market, made from high-grade 7075 AL for unparalleled strength and durability. Not only do Swings Spacers enhance the aesthetics of your skates with their mesmerizing design, but they also optimize performance on the rink. Experience the perfect balance of lightness and strength, embodied in these golden-hued spacers. Upgrade your skating setup with Swings Spacers – where craftsmanship meets innovation, and every detail is a testament to excellence.
Included Accessories: AL spacers, mounting screws, tool -Torx T25

Powerslide Accell Carbon 13.2 / 4x110

High-Performance\, All-Carbon Racing Frame

Strong\, Lightweight Carbon Frame

Your dreams have come true with the all-new Accell Carbon 13.2 / 4x110 inline race frame from Powerslide. Inspired by the famous ICON frame\, imagine how fast you can ACCELERATE out of corners with this rigid compression-molded carbon frame that weighs only 155g. 

Unstoppable Speed and Control!

Designed around the trustworthy 195 mounting standards\, the Powerslide Accell Carbon 13.2 / 4x110 frame gives skaters a responsive push while the stiffer back portion of the frame still allows you to turn quickly through sharp corners as the front portion of the frame gives you superb flex for improved comfort and overall performance.

Mount the Powerslide Accell Carbon 13.2 / 4x110 frame on your favorite race boot and get the coolest skate of the peloton.

<div class=""block_content_description to-read-more expanded"">The MG Frame frame collection is one of the most recognized and successful inline race frames. Designed to deliver efficient power transfer with every stride, the MG Frame 4x110, 13,2"" frame will help you reach the top of the podium in no time.Introducing the revolutionary Swings Speed Frames: meticulously crafted from the finest-grade Magnesium, each frame is fully extruded and precision-machined to absolute perfection. Every surface and edge is a testament to the artistry of CNC work, embodying Bart's vision of a frame that's both supremely stiff and feather-light.

Engineered for optimum performance, these frames feature wider deck mounting for flawless power transfer and direct flat side walls for an exceptionally efficient push. The attention to detail is unparalleled, with an exquisite finish and intricate printed designs showcasing Swings' dedication to craftsmanship.

Available in a range of sizes, the Swings Speed Frames are already making waves in the racing scene, proving their worth on the track even before their official release. With their low profile, lightweight construction, and unbeatable stiffness, these frames offer seamless edge-to-edge movement and unparalleled push efficiency.

Designed to provide stiffness where it's needed and flexibility where it counts, the Swings Speed Frames are set to revolutionize the world of speed skating. Experience the difference for yourself and elevate your performance to new heights with Swings.

Introducing Swings Speed Axles: the epitome of lightweight performance and precision engineering. Crafted from premium AL 7075 aluminum, these axles boast a CNC-cut middle section, ensuring optimal weight reduction without compromising strength.

Finished to perfection with a luxurious gold anodized coating, Swings Speed Axles not only enhance the aesthetics of your skates but also elevate your performance on the track. Their lightweight design reduces rotational mass, allowing for quicker acceleration and smoother transitions.

Engineered for durability and speed, these axles provide the perfect balance of strength and agility. Whether you're racing towards the finish line or mastering intricate maneuvers, Swings Speed Axles deliver unparalleled performance with every stride.
Upgrade your skating experience with Swings Speed Axles – where lightness meets strength, and performance meets perfection.
Introducing Swings Spacers – a masterpiece of precision engineering. Each spacer is meticulously crafted with a 360° CNC cut, creating a stunning visual reminiscent of a saw cutting through wood.
Designed with a focus on weight reduction, these spacers are the epitome of lightweight performance. Weighing in at only 1.0g.
